Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?fix:=20adiciona=20servi=C3=A7o=20de=20frontend?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20ao=20docker-compose=20(estava=20faltando)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

O Dockerfile do frontend (Vite + nginx) já existia na raiz do projeto,
mas o docker-compose.yml só buildava o backend. Sem o serviço de
frontend e a rota Traefik para fotografia.fbautomacao.space, o app não
tinha como ser acessado publicamente via Dokploy.
---
 docker-compose.yml | 17 +++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 17 insertions(+)

diff --git a/docker-compose.yml b/docker-compose.yml
index b53d3ce..b132de6 100644
--- a/docker-compose.yml
+++ b/docker-compose.yml
@@ -45,6 +45,23 @@ services:
       - "traefik.http.routers.foto-agenda-api.tls.certresolver=letsencrypt"
       - "traefik.http.services.foto-agenda-api.loadbalancer.server.port=8000"
 
+  frontend:
+    build:
+      context: .
+      dockerfile: Dockerfile
+      args:
+        - VITE_API_URL=https://api.fotografia.fbautomacao.space
+    restart: unless-stopped
+    depends_on:
+      - backend
+    networks:
+      - kairos_network
+    labels:
+      - "traefik.enable=true"
+      - "traefik.http.routers.foto-agenda.rule=Host(`fotografia.fbautomacao.space`)"
+      - "traefik.http.routers.foto-agenda.tls.certresolver=letsencrypt"
+      - "traefik.http.services.foto-agenda.loadbalancer.server.port=80"
+
 volumes:
   postgres_data:
 
